<br>
    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Well,strategy eh. I have only been playing a month. So if this looks like a random pile,that is because it is. Hence,the name. Actually,i put in alot of companions,so that i could get them out fast,and i put in weapons for them to help keep them alive,and so i could constintly be drawing more cards. The only events i use are 2 x ranger&#39;s versatility,to make me safe at the later sites,and 2 secret sentinels,to kill armories,or any other random conditions that make me angry. I only use those 4 because i do not like drawing them and having them sit in my hand forever.<br>
<br>
Shadow i decided to use urak,because i learned with the aragorn starter deck,and they seemed so brutal,so i went with them. Plus savagery kicks ass!!!<br>
<br>
To start,i bid 5,so that i can go 1st. Then i pull sam,and take off my burdens,and generally just let him die early on so i can put out other companions,and not fear savagery,and random other stupid cards. <br>
<br>
If i play against any orcs,i will just put out whoever i have usually.<br>
<br>
I will usually move from 1 to 3 1st turn,and heal at the sanctuary. Then i usually do not double move until site 5,because at 6 i can use all my companions to soak up the minions. Then heal again. I will usually stop at 8 also.<br>
<br>
Card choices.<br>
<br>
I went with the tale of gil galad,and the saga of elendil because they can make it so i can draw more,and they give me one more vitality,which is huge with bows.<br>
<br>
I used no business of ours,because mirror of galadriel was huge in people&#39;s decks in the open. <br>
<br>
I used saruman&#39;s power to kill random conditions. Helped out quitew a bit actually!<br>
<br>
I only used one spies of saruman,because i only had one. It works out huge at rivers,to stop the ranger&#39;s versatility tricks.<br>
<br>
The deck worked out really well,for my 1st ever attempt at making a lotr deck. I have only been playing a month,and going 4-2 in an open,as your 1st event is not bad. It is also really fun to play.<br>
<br>
Any help will be great. Thanks for reading all.<br>
<br>
Brian Fred-aka (john matrix) </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
